&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Ensure the accuracy of all financial statements, providing the leadership team with the clear, data-backed insights needed to make high-stakes decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Gatekeeping:&lt;/strong&gt; Manage day-to-day expense approvals, ensuring all spend—from travel and flight bookings to vendor payments—aligns with our internal policies and reflects &quot;best judgment&quot; for company dollars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Integrity:&lt;/strong&gt; Maintain an accurate general ledger of transactions and reconciliations, identifying and resolving discrepancies with surgical precision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AR/AP processing:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop a scalable process and ensure prompt execution for processing receivables and payable for the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Architecture:&lt;/strong&gt; Play a key role in the design and implementation of our next-generation ERP system, helping us move away from early-stage tools into a modern scalable financial ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Audit &amp;amp; Compliance:&lt;/strong&gt; Support for company’s first accounting audit, subsequently maintaining a &quot;permanent-readiness&quot; posture and ensuring full compliance with GAAP and industry-specific standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education:&lt;/strong&gt; A Bachelor’s degree with 5+ years of professional experience or an associate&#39;s degree with 10+ years of experience, preferably in accounting/finance. professional experience in high growth technology or government contracting is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
